Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.29,0:00:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} It's the ponies{\i0}\N{\i1} from my old village.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.89,0:00:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's only a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.30,0:00:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,With my past, I should never\Nbe in charge of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.96,0:00:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,THEY'VE TAKEN MY SISTER AND I!\NIT'S WORSE THAN LAST TIME!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.31,0:00:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Chrysalis and the\NChangelings are back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.42,0:00:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They've ponynapped all of\Nthe most powerful ponies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.77,0:00:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.11,0:00:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Thorax. He's\Na reformed Changeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.39,0:00:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They took Fluttershy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.89,0:00:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I have a pretty good\Nidea where she might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.83,0:00:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Regular subtitles\NBy YayPonies\N♪♪ My Little Changeling, Feeding is Magic ♪♪\Nhttps://yp1.yayponies.eu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is so strange.\NWe're here and that's there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.82,0:01:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I clearly meant for us\Nto be there and not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.41,0:01:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can probably\Nexplain that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.61,0:01:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well, if at first\Nyou don't succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.52,0:01:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should come\Nup with a plan first?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.98,0:01:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.96,0:01:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, figuring out the\Nbest way to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.46,0:01:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,before you actually do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.03,0:01:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you see, unlike\Nyou I can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.75,0:01:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.65,0:01:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all very nice, but\Nreally a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.55,0:01:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.92,0:01:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And what else could\Nwe possibly need?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.50,0:01:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A draconequis with magic AND\Nhalf a brain might help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.74,0:02:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here\Nagain?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.52,0:02:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's not like you're\Ngoing to stop the Changelings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.65,0:02:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by pulling a rabbit\Nout of the hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.73,0:02:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At least my magic\Ncan do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.64,0:02:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing about\Nmagic here is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.69,0:02:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For Fluttershy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.77,0:02:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.15,0:02:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing other than\NChangeling magic works here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Chrysalis' throne is carved\Nfrom an ancient dark stone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.43,0:02:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that soaks up outside magic\Nthe same way Changelings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.26,0:02:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,soak up love. It's how\Nshe keeps the hive safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.84,0:02:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So... What kind of\Nplan were you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Without magic I have no idea.\NBut nopony else is coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so somepony better\Ncome up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anypony?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.31,0:02:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Anything?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.35,0:03:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This throne. If we get into\Nthe hive and destroy it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.89,0:03:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can we get our magic back?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a terrible plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we even supposed\Nto get to the hive?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.89,0:03:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.69,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't walked that\Nfar in millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. I don't know how any\Nof you manage not being able
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.63,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to disappear and reappear\Nwhenever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I for one definitely miss\Nyou being able to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.69,0:03:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Give Discord a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us knew we weren't\Ngoing to be able to use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.70,0:03:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.09,0:03:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get separated, it might\Nmake sense to have a way
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.69,0:03:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure we are\Nwho we say we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooo. Like a secret code.\NHow about if I say "We are"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you say "Doomed?" Or you say\N"Rescue" and I say "I'm--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How about if we say "Klutzy"\Nand you say "Draconequis?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.74,0:04:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Klutzy draconequis.\NWorks for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.59,0:04:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll definitely\Nremember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.41,0:04:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}OK. I am definitely{\i0}\N{\i1}glad you came.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.88,0:04:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think we'd be able\Nto find our way without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.67,0:04:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You definitely wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.71,0:04:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Where's the way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Changeling Hive. It\Nshifts and changes like we do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.20,0:04:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're the only ones\Nwho can navigate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.36,0:04:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's total chaos to\Nnon-Changelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.02,0:04:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's decent chaos. I don't\Nknow if I'd call it total.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.19,0:04:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we sure that\NI'll get my magic back
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.38,0:04:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when we destroy\Nthis throne-thingy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If Thorax is\Nright, then yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.09,0:04:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.47,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And how are we supposed\Nto destroy the throne
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:04:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when we find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.62,0:05:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I... don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.20,0:05:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose you brought\Nany throne-destroying tools
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.48,0:05:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,along with these\Nuseless side show props?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.60,0:05:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Asks the "lord of chaos"\Nwho can't go for a walk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.86,0:05:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,without whining non-stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but when the\Nthrone is destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.30,0:05:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'LL be able to rip the\Nvery fabric of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to save our friends\Nwhile YOU'LL still be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.31,0:05:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a self-absorbed,\Nbelow-average illusionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.74,0:05:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,SELF-ABSORBED?! Why you--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.70,0:05:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,CUT! IT! OUT!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.08,0:05:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just barely\Nkeeping it together
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.80,0:05:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would be WONDERFUL if you\Ntwo could actually try to help
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of bickering like foals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.06,0:05:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.47,0:05:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we help?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.79,0:05:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me! I couldn't\Neven handle giving advice
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.68,0:05:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Sunset Festival\Nand I HAD magic then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the three of us\Nare as good as useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:05:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At least Thorax knows\Nwhere we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.74,0:06:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Um... guys?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.14,0:06:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.78,0:06:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Aww, great!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.56,0:06:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We might as well just\Nsit here and wait
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.79,0:06:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Changelings to\Nsoak up all of our love
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.66,0:06:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever gross thing\Nit is that they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How often do you\Nall get hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.89,0:06:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I haven't\Nbeen since I met Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.38,0:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Changelings\Nare always hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.78,0:06:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We can never get\Nenough love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's just super.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.72,0:06:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But you aren't\Nhungry at all now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.71,0:06:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I made a few friends,\NI guess I just sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,forgot about the\Nwhole feeding thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.46,0:06:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that about the same\Ntime your wings changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.38,0:06:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.81,0:06:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,While I would love to\Nsit around chit-chatting
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.44,0:06:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about feeding and\Nnot feeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.75,0:06:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a FLUTTERSHY to save!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.92,0:06:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please lower your voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.16,0:06:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to get\Nus all captured!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.29,0:07:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! You keep saying\Nthat, but I haven't seen
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.30,0:07:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,an actual Changeling since\Nwe got into this hive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.71,0:07:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A CHANGELING PATROL!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.28,0:07:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This seems like one of those\Nmoments where we need a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.08,0:07:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.65,0:07:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no magic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.74,0:07:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's not like my illusions\Nare going to save us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any of\Nyour smoke bombs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.82,0:07:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.92,0:07:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking for somepony?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.34,0:07:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the best\Nyou've got? Hahaha!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.78,0:07:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not exactly Great and\NPowerful, but effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.11,0:07:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mh, I'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.82,0:08:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Klutzy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.13,0:08:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Draconequis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.11,0:08:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I really think we\Nneed a new code word.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.00,0:08:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a pretty\Ngood plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.94,0:08:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still don't\Nknow where we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.12,0:08:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Actually, we might.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of the Changelings\Ndidn't go with the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! With an intruder\Nin the hive,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.96,0:08:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they went to\Nprotect the Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.22,0:08:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thinking,\NStarlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.13,0:08:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I wanted to, there's\Nno way past the guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.58,0:08:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be spotted for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.50,0:08:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We need some kind\Nof distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.21,0:08:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fresh out of\Nsmoke bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally I'm the most\Ndistracting thing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.47,0:08:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can think of, but\Nwithout magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.94,0:09:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't\Nunderestimate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Changelings and\NChangelettes, believe me;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.07,0:09:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just as surprised\Nas you are that I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard that I'd be playing\Nfor a bunch of Changelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.56,0:09:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was beside myself. Then I\Nrealized it was just one of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.66,0:09:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But seriously, this\Nisn't the toughest crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.49,0:09:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've ever been in front of,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.85,0:09:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's definitely\Nthe easiest to bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.41,0:09:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To bug...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.48,0:09:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this thing on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.96,0:09:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you think that\Nyou can do any better,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,be my guest!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.59,0:09:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It is absolutely ridiculous\Nthat that worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.00,0:09:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It is certainly a pleasure\Nto have such dedicated fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.35,0:09:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to come back\Nwith some new material
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.00,0:10:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,after I rescue Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.22,0:10:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Please... Help...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.43,0:10:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Discord! I'm stuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.03,0:10:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You certainly are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.34,0:10:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I should probably\Nhelp you get free, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.44,0:10:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.03,0:10:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.44,0:10:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are obviously\Nnot Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.21,0:10:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.24,0:10:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm separated\Nfrom the group
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.96,0:10:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and just happen to come across\Nthe one pony I care most about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.28,0:10:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I can smell this\Nset-up a mile away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.00,0:10:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you\Nshould trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go find the\Nothers. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.93,0:10:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.16,0:10:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're probably\Nall Changelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.73,0:10:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't\Nrescue any of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.87,0:11:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you think maybe one of us\Nmight be the real Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.57,0:11:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That certainly would be a nasty\NChangeling trick, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.76,0:11:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.95,0:11:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.79,0:11:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the real\NFluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.30,0:11:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't wait for Discord.\NBetween seeing him and Trixie,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.08,0:11:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the castle will be\Ncrawling with guards soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.34,0:11:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we do manage to\Ndestroy Chrysalis' throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.22,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He could take on the\Nentire Changeling army
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.02,0:11:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by sneezing if he\Nwanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably already\Nbeen captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.70,0:11:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Fellow rescuers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.40,0:11:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't stay here. We've\Ngot to find the throne!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.32,0:11:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oooh! I heard some\Nof the Changelings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.08,0:11:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who were chasing me say\Nthat they know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.48,0:11:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Klutzy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.61,0:11:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmmm? Oh, yeah haha. I can\Nbe klutzy. Now, follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.18,0:11:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that's\Nnot Discord, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.21,0:12:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.25,0:12:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This way! We're\Nalmost there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.26,0:12:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this trick. If\Nhe says to go left,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.82,0:12:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we should definitely go right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.57,0:12:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He's leading us to a\Nswarm waiting to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, I'll handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.80,0:12:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You two just get ready to\Nrun into the other tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.29,0:12:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, what!? Trixie\Nyou can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't know what to do.\NWe've already lost Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.72,0:12:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't lose you too.\NWithout magic I--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.03,0:12:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, you got us this\Nfar with just my illusions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.35,0:12:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and Discord's\Nannoying personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.75,0:12:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need magic to\Nfigure out what to do next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.79,0:12:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're afraid\Nto be in charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.18,0:12:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're really good at it.\NListen to your best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.83,0:12:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Discord? Wanna see the new\Ntrick I've been working on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.67,0:12:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I call it, "The\NChangeling Catcher!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.10,0:12:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One little pony\Nall by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how will I ever\Nprevent this daring rescue?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.55,0:14:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, well. The Princess\Nof Friendship's sole pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.48,0:14:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I didn't think\Nyou were worth replacing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.93,0:14:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with one of my drones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.77,0:14:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.98,0:14:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I already have. Nopony\Nis coming to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.36,0:14:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Your little squad was it,\Nand now there's just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.28,0:14:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorax is still out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mention that traitor's\Nname in my Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a fool to leave and\Neven more a fool to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.70,0:14:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When I find him he'll\Nlearn just what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.61,0:14:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to those who betray the hive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.46,0:14:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems I don't\Nhave far to look, do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.61,0:14:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorax!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Very clever. And clearly Thorax\Nrevealed to you the secret
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.09,0:15:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of my throne. I can't\Nhave powerful ponies
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,using their\Nabilities against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.06,0:15:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with your\Nrather embarrassing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.15,0:15:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,little rescue attempt,\Neverything has gone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.97,0:15:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,according to MY plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.79,0:15:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What plan? Why did\Nyou do all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.46,0:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So I could feed, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.62,0:15:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,By replacing the most beloved\Nfigures in Equestria,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,my drones will be able to store\Nall the love meant for them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.26,0:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and return it here... to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony will do as I\Ncommand and my subjects
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will feed on their love\Nfor generations!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.78,0:15:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you\Ndidn't have to?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.05,0:15:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.66,0:16:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The hunger of Changelings\Ncan never be satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.92,0:16:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Thorax left the\Nhive and made a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.87,0:16:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He shared love and now\Nhe doesn't need to feed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.51,0:16:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to live your\Nlives starving all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know nothing\Nof the Changelings
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.91,0:16:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or what it takes\Nto be their Queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I decide what is best for my\Nsubjects, not some mewling grub!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.41,0:16:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it's like to lead\Nby fear and intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.97,0:16:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know\Nwhat it's like
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.55,0:16:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to want everypony\Nto do what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.16,0:16:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was wrong. A real leader\Ndoesn't force her subjects
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.17,0:16:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to deny who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.08,0:16:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She celebrates what\Nmakes them unique...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.69,0:16:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,...and listens when one of\Nthem finds a better way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing\NThorax has found...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.74,0:16:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...is what happens to those who\Nturn their back on the hive!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.38,0:16:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.87,0:16:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as soon as I drain every\Nlast ounce of love from him
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:17:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and show my subjects\Nwhat a real leader is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.65,0:17:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel the love\Ninside me slipping away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.06,0:17:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hold onto\Nit much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.71,0:17:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.33,0:17:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharing love is what made\Nyou different to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You should share\Nyours with Chrysalis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Give her all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.55,0:17:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what happens\Nwhen you give love freely
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of taking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.85,0:18:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, um, good to see you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.68,0:18:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.56,0:18:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We defeated the Changelings\Nwith no magic at all;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.99,0:18:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they found a new leader...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.68,0:18:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're all\Nkinda good now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.62,0:18:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Starlight Glimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.27,0:18:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems as though you've\Nlearned a great deal
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.99,0:18:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,since we last spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.25,0:18:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When Twilight and her\Nfriends defeated me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.21,0:19:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I chose to run away and seek\Nrevenge. You don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.42,0:19:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be the leader\Nyour subjects deserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no revenge you\Ncould ever conceive of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.32,0:19:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that will come close to\Nwhat I will exact upon you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.89,0:19:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,one day, Starlight Glimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.15,0:19:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorax, as the new leader\Nof the Changelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to discussing how\Nwe can improve our relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.99,0:19:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.83,0:19:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for the moment,\Nperhaps it is best
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.63,0:19:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that we leave the Changeling\NKingdom to the Changelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid idea!\NNow who's ready
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.47,0:19:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for some celebratory\Ntea at Fluttershy's?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.78,0:19:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Um. Everypony?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.87,0:19:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, now that you\Ncan snap your claws
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.40,0:19:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and send us absolutely\Nanywhere again,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:19:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I have a\Nbetter option.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.84,0:20:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.. Hey Starlight.\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.54,0:20:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You left in such\Na hurry before,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.69,0:20:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we kinda thought you\Ndidn't want to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I guess after the way I\Nused my magic on all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.02,0:20:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure I was somepony\Nwho should even be in charge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.45,0:20:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of a baking contest. I was\Nafraid I might go back
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.71,0:20:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to being the pony I\Nused to be. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.08,0:20:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...I realized that sometimes\Nyou don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.14,0:20:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to step up. And I\NHAVE changed. I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.18,0:20:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether than means saving\NEquestria OR helping friends
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.89,0:20:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with a sunset festival.\NSpeaking of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.73,0:20:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...I know the festival is almost\Nover, but I kinda invited
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.40,0:20:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a few of my\Nfriends to join.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.47,0:20:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope that's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.61,0:20:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding? Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.97,0:20:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. Now, where's\Nthat baking contest?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.21,0:20:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This pony needs a cupcake!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.26,0:21:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm able to rip the very\Nfabric of reality again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.97,0:21:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah and I'm\Nstill a self-absorbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.98,0:21:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,below-average\Nillusionist. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.53,0:21:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I was going to say\Na COUPLE of those illusions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.44,0:21:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,were slightly above average.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ever need a little chaos\Nin your act, let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.70,0:21:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha! When pigs fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wish is my command!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.40,0:21:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa-whoaaaa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.40,0:21:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Somepony is really gonna have to\Ncatch us up on what we missed.
